<TITLE> 88 teachers promoted to professor </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 25 (bdnews24.com)  Eighty-eight teachers from the BCS education cadre in government colleges have been promoted to professor, the Ministry of Education said in a circular Monday. The promoted teachers have been directed to take up their new positions by March 6. Eleven of the new professors come from economic departments, seven from English, nine from Bangla, four from history, two from Islamic history and culture and eight from political science. Three come from philosophy, one from sociology, two from social welfare, one from Arabic, one from Islamic studies, 10 from physics, six from chemistry, and three from botany. Six of the promoted teachers come from zoology, three from mathematics, three from geography, one from home economics, five from accounting and two from management. bdnews
